Comment:
For all the people saying it's a ripoff of Zootopia, Kubo and the two strings, Kung Fu panda etc here are some facts:

-This movie is based off a graphic novel from 2009.

-The movie came out in China in June 2016, and was being worked on for over 5 years (That was before Sing and Kubo and the Two Strings came out)

-Animal movies have been around forever

So I hope you understand that this is not a ripoff at all, and it was a coincidence that these other movies came out before Rock Dog!

Title: Rock Dog Official Trailer #1 (2017) Luke Wilson, Eddie Izzard Animated Movie HD
Comment:
I don't want to jump to conclusions just from watching a mere trailer, but this movie looks so....mediocre. I wish that commercials would not reveal SO MUCH about their movies - it completely RUINS the experience! That's why I was able to enjoy Zootopia; because the trailer was so misleading. I didn't know that piece would actual be about discrimination and race, I thought it was just a cute, well animated movie. It didn't show its entire plot in the trailer.
We all know we have seen this type of story before: a protagonist has his future planned out for him, but he wants to do something else, so he leaves his home to follow his dreams...you get the idea. I can honestly predict this entire movie in my head - it's the same situation with Sing. 

Besides the plot, this film is so lazily animated - it resembles Norm of the North, appearance wise. It's definitely not the WORST animation I have seen, but you can tell that the people behind this movie didn't try their best on the scenery. Perhaps they were on a budget cut - who knows?

Not only that, but the jokes I am observing in this trailer are so predictable and over-used....if you want comic relief, don't use moments that have been used for years - make your own ORIGINAL humor. Even movies for kids deserve to have an actual funny scenes.

But who am I to assume this movie will be so average? Maybe it will be better than I expected. (Personally, I know for sure that the British cat will be the saving grace of Rock Dog)
